  path: preprocessing_data_from_arup.parquet
meta:
  name:
    en: Preprocessing data from Arup
  identifier: cork/preprocessing_data_from_arup
  description:
    en: "on_road_transport_emissions_ktco2e - Metric: on_road_transport_emissions_ktco2e
      - Source: CorkCity_BEI_v2_On-road Transport_20260323.xlsx - 2023: 288.4812283
      - On-Road Transport Emissions, all modes (Calculation!F115/F164/F189)<br/>vehicle_emissions_share
      - Metric: vehicle_emissions_share - transport_mode: cars - Source: Arup assumption
      - 2023: 56.57145285 - Passenger Car - share of on-road emissions (Calculation!F116)<br/>vehicle_emissions_share
      - Metric: vehicle_emissions_share - transport_mode: light_trucks - Source: Arup
      assumption - 2023: 7.707832719 - Light Duty Vehicles - share of on-road emissions
      (Calculation!F165)<br/>vehicle_emissions_share - Metric: vehicle_emissions_share
      - transport_mode: heavy_trucks - Source: Arup assumption - 2023: 20.52949368
      - Heavy Duty Vehicles - share of on-road emissions (Calculation!F190)<br/>bus_emissions_tco2e
      - Metric: bus_emissions_tco2e - transport_mode: buses - Source: Bus Éireann
      Fleet Transition - CorkCity - 2023: 7835 - Total carbon emissions - Buses (Calculation!F129)<br/>vehicle_km
      - Metric: vehicle_km - transport_mode: cars - Source: CorkCity_BEI_v2_On-road
      Transport_20260323.xlsx; Road Traffic Volumes - 2023: 1486020672 - Annual Total
      vehicle-km travelled by Passenger Cars (Calculation!F50)<br/>vehicle_km - Metric:
      vehicle_km - transport_mode: buses - Source: Bus Éireann Fleet Transition -
      CorkCity - 2023: 8309305 - Approx Annual KMs (buses) (Calculation!F76)<br/>goods_vehicles_number
      - Metric: goods_vehicles_number - Source: CorkCity_BEI_v2_On-road Transport_20260323.xlsx
      - 2023: 16502.42454 - Goods Vehicles - number (Calculation!F176/F201)<br/>freight_weight_class_share
      - Metric: freight_weight_class_share - transport_mode: light_trucks - Source:
      Cork Goods Vehicles 2023.xlsx - 2023: 89.35372684 - Share of Light Duty Transport
      <3.5t (Calculation!F174)<br/>freight_weight_class_share - Metric: freight_weight_class_share
      - transport_mode: heavy_trucks - Source: Cork Goods Vehicles 2023.xlsx - 2023:
      10.64627316 - Share of Heavy Duty Transport >3.5t (Calculation!F199)<br/>avg_km_per_goods_vehicle
      - Metric: avg_km_per_goods_vehicle - Source: Road Traffic Volumes - 2023: 20929
      - Good Vehicle - Average Kilometres Travelled (Calculation!F181/F206)<br/>car_commuters_driver_and_passenger
      - Metric: car_commuters_driver_and_passenger - Source: Usually resident by means
      of travel to work, school, college or childcare - 2023: 82305 - Car Driver +
      Passenger - Daily Commuting to Work (Calculation!F44)<br/>car_commuters_driver_only
      - Metric: car_commuters_driver_only - Source: Usually resident by means of travel
      to work, school, college or childcare - 2023: 52852 - Car Driver - Daily Commuting
      to Work (Calculation!F45)<br/>avg_trip_distance_km - Metric: avg_trip_distance_km
      - Source: National Household Travel Survey - Research Report 2024 - 2023: 9.06
      - Average Trip Distance (Calculation!F62/F71, shared by bus and rail)<br/>bus_annual_passenger_journeys
      - Metric: bus_annual_passenger_journeys - Source: Bus and Rail Statistics for
      Ireland - Statistical Bulletin 2023 - 2023: 16.2 - Bus - Cork Commuter Annual
      Passenger Journeys, millions (Calculation!F61)<br/>cork_kent_passenger_journeys
      - Metric: cork_kent_passenger_journeys - Source: Cork City Council_BEI_v2_Rail,
      Aviation and Ports_20260323.xlsx - 2023: 3.37415 - Total Cork Kent-related passenger
      journeys, millions (Calculation!F68)<br/>national_freight_demand_total - Metric:
      national_freight_demand_total - Source: Road Freight Transport Activity - 2023:
      12596 - Total transport demand (all weight) - baseline, National (Calculation!F219/F227)<br/>cork_share_of_national_fleet
      - Metric: cork_share_of_national_fleet - Source: CorkCity_BEI_v2_On-road Transport_20260323.xlsx;
      Road Freight Transport Activity - 2023: 4.123245576 - Cork City share of National
      Goods Vehicles (Calculation!F217)<br/>local_heating_by_carrier_gwh - Metric:
      local_heating_by_carrier_gwh - energy_carrier: fossil - fuel_type: fossil -
      Source: Heating and cooling in Ireland today - Space Heating and How water demand
      (SEAI) - 2023: 42303 - Fossil - Local Heating - National (Calculation!F491)<br/>local_heating_by_carrier_gwh
      - Metric: local_heating_by_carrier_gwh - energy_carrier: electricity - fuel_type:
      non_fossil - Source: Heating and cooling in Ireland today - Space Heating and
      How water demand (SEAI) - 2023: 7426 - Electricity - Local Heating - National
      (Calculation!F519)<br/>local_heating_by_carrier_gwh - Metric: local_heating_by_carrier_gwh
      - energy_carrier: bioenergy - fuel_type: non_fossil - Source: Heating and cooling
      in Ireland today - Space Heating and How water demand (SEAI) - 2023: 2056 -
      Biobased - Local Heating - National (Calculation!F541)<br/>total_local_heating_gwh
      - Metric: total_local_heating_gwh - Source: Heating and cooling in Ireland today
      - Space Heating and How water demand (SEAI) - 2023: 52375 - Total - Local Heating
      - National (Calculation!F449). Reused by group 19 (district heating target share)
      as the same denominator.<br/>residential_buildings_energy_gwh - Metric: residential_buildings_energy_gwh
      - Source: CorkCity_BEI_Residential_DRAFT_20260327.xlsx - 2023: 1613.747936 -
      Residential Buildings - Total Energy (Calculation!F377)<br/>commercial_buildings_energy_gwh
      - Metric: commercial_buildings_energy_gwh - Source: CorkCity_BEI_v3_Commercial
      and Industrial_20260325.xlsx - 2023: 752 - Commercial Buildings - Total Energy
      (Calculation!F378)<br/>industrial_buildings_energy_gwh - Metric: industrial_buildings_energy_gwh
      - Source: CorkCity_BEI_v3_Commercial and Industrial_20260325.xlsx - 2023: 11.5
      - Industrial Buildings - Total Energy (Calculation!F379)<br/>public_buildings_natgas_gwh
      - Metric: public_buildings_natgas_gwh - Source: GHG targets - detailed data
      Export.xlsx - 2023: 9.091071286 - Public Services Buildings - Total Energy -
      Natural Gas (Calculation!F380)<br/>public_buildings_electricity_gwh - Metric:
      public_buildings_electricity_gwh - Source: GHG targets - detailed data Export.xlsx
      - 2023: 17.29835167 - Public Services Buildings - Total Energy - Net electricity
      imports (Calculation!F381)<br/>share_of_heating_demand_national - Metric: share_of_heating_demand_national
      - Source: Energy in Ireland 2025 Report - SEAI - 2023: 75.43476901 - Share of
      Heating Demand - National (Calculation!F384)<br/>residential_floor_area_m2 -
      Metric: residential_floor_area_m2 - Source: CorkCity_BEI_Residential_DRAFT_20260327.xlsx
      - 2023: 4313922.273 - Residential - Floor Area, sum of detached/semi-detached/apartment
      (Calculation!F258)<br/>non_residential_floor_area_m2 - Metric: non_residential_floor_area_m2
      - Source: CorkCity_BEI_v3_Commercial and Industrial_20260325.xlsx - 2023: 1815758.663
      - Total Non-Residential Floor Area (Calculation!F261)<br/>public_floor_area_m2
      - Metric: public_floor_area_m2 - Source: DRAFT Building Action List.xlsx - 2023:
      58394 - Public Buildings - Total Floor Area (Calculation!F262)<br/>residential_electricity_gwh
      - Metric: residential_electricity_gwh - Source: CorkCity_BEI_Residential_DRAFT_20260327.xlsx;
      Energy in Ireland 2025 Report - SEAI - 2023: 396.4209082 - Residential Buildings
      - Total electricity (Calculation!F606)<br/>commercial_electricity_gwh - Metric:
      commercial_electricity_gwh - Source: CorkCity_BEI_v3_Commercial and Industrial_20260325.xlsx;
      Energy in Ireland 2025 Report - SEAI - 2023: 184.730537 - Commercial Buildings
      - Total electricity (Calculation!F607)<br/>industrial_electricity_gwh - Metric:
      industrial_electricity_gwh - Source: CorkCity_BEI_v3_Commercial and Industrial_20260325.xlsx;
      Energy in Ireland 2025 Report - SEAI - 2023: 2.825001564 - Industrial Buildings
      - Total electricity (Calculation!F608)<br/>public_electricity_gwh - Metric:
      public_electricity_gwh - Source: Cork City Council_BEI_v2_Public Services_20260320.xlsx
      - 2023: 18.224369 - Public Buildings - Electricity (Calculation!F609)<br/>transport_sector_electricity_gwh
      - Metric: transport_sector_electricity_gwh - Source: CorkCity_BEI_v2_On-road
      Transport_20260323.xlsx; Energy in Ireland 2025 Report - SEAI - 2023: 13.9721756
      - Transport sector - Total electricity (Calculation!F610)<br/>buildings_built_all_ber
      - Metric: buildings_built_all_ber - Source: Domestic Building Energy Rating
      - 2023: 28 - Number of Buildings Built - All BER Rating (Calculation!F355/F363)<br/>buildings_built_minimum_standard
      - Metric: buildings_built_minimum_standard - Source: Domestic Building Energy
      Rating - 2023: 1 - Number of Buildings Built - minimum standard, today (Calculation!F356)<br/>buildings_built_better_than_minimum
      - Metric: buildings_built_better_than_minimum - Source: Domestic Building Energy
      Rating - 2023: 27 - Number of Buildings Built - better than minimum standard,
      today (Calculation!F364)<br/>top_performance_standard_target_share - Metric:
      top_performance_standard_target_share - Source: Introduction – Technology and
      Innovation Pathways for Zero-carbon-ready Buildings by 2030 – Analysis - IEA
      - 2030: 100 - Top performing building standard - Zero-Carbon-Emission by Target
      Year (Calculation!F1033)<br/>avg_oil_price_c_per_kwh - Metric: avg_oil_price_c_per_kwh
      - Source: Energy price trends - 2023: 12.13 - Average Oil - Household fuel price
      (Calculation!F774)<br/>avg_gas_price_c_per_kwh - Metric: avg_gas_price_c_per_kwh
      - Source: Energy price trends - 2023: 15.595 - Average Gas - Household fuel
      price (Calculation!F780)<br/>avg_heating_electricity_price_c_per_kwh - Metric:
      avg_heating_electricity_price_c_per_kwh - Source: Energy price trends - 2023:
      32.415 - Average Electricity - Household fuel price (Calculation!F786)<br/>avg_wood_price_c_per_kwh
      - Metric: avg_wood_price_c_per_kwh - Source: Energy price trends - 2023: 12.2975
      - Average Wood - Household fuel price (Calculation!F792)<br/>electricity_price_s1_c_per_kwh
      - Metric: electricity_price_s1_c_per_kwh - Source: Energy price trends - 2023:
      27.35 - Average electricity price to households - S1 (Calculation!F761)<br/>electricity_price_s2_c_per_kwh
      - Metric: electricity_price_s2_c_per_kwh - Source: Energy price trends - 2023:
      37.48 - Average electricity price to households - S2 (Calculation!F762)<br/>modal_share_existing
      - Metric: modal_share_existing - transport_mode: walking - Source: 4. Transport
      and Mobility | Cork City Council's Online Consultation Portal - 2023: 21 - Walking
      - Modal Share - Reference Existing Year (Calculation!F888)<br/>modal_share_target_ref
      - Metric: modal_share_target_ref - transport_mode: walking - Source: 4. Transport
      and Mobility | Cork City Council's Online Consultation Portal - 2030: 21 - Walking
      - Modal Share - Reference Target Year (Calculation!F889)<br/>modal_share_existing
      - Metric: modal_share_existing - transport_mode: cycling - Source: 4. Transport
      and Mobility | Cork City Council's Online Consultation Portal - 2023: 1 - Cycling
      - Modal Share - Reference Existing Year (Calculation!F892)<br/>modal_share_target_ref
      - Metric: modal_share_target_ref - transport_mode: cycling - Source: 4. Transport
      and Mobility | Cork City Council's Online Consultation Portal - 2030: 4 - Cycling
      - Modal Share - Reference Target Year (Calculation!F893)<br/>modal_share_existing
      - Metric: modal_share_existing - transport_mode: public_transport - Source:
      4. Transport and Mobility | Cork City Council's Online Consultation Portal -
      2023: 10 - Public Transport - Modal Share - Reference Existing Year (Calculation!F896)<br/>modal_share_target_ref
      - Metric: modal_share_target_ref - transport_mode: public_transport - Source:
      4. Transport and Mobility | Cork City Council's Online Consultation Portal -
      2030: 25.7 - Public Transport - Modal Share - Reference Target Year (Calculation!F897)<br/>district_heating_target_twh
      - Metric: district_heating_target_twh - Source: A REVIEW OF RESIDENTIAL HEAT
      DECARBONISATION IN IRELAND - 2030: 2.7 - District Heating - Target Year (Calculation!F1038)<br/>total_residential_buildings_units
      - Metric: total_residential_buildings_units - Source: CorkCity_BEI_Residential_DRAFT_20260327.xlsx
      - 2023: 84368 - Total Residential buildings - units (Calculation!F341)<br/>housing_units_retrofitted_per_year
      - Metric: housing_units_retrofitted_per_year - Source: Cork City Council Secures
      €2m grant from the European Investment Bank to accelerate retrofitting - 2023:
      150 - Housing Stock - Retrofitting (Calculation!F344)<br/>avg_retrofits_per_annum_target
      - Metric: avg_retrofits_per_annum_target - Source: A REVIEW OF RESIDENTIAL HEAT
      DECARBONISATION IN IRELAND - 2030: 75000 - Average number of retrofits/renovations
      per annum required up to Target Year, National (Calculation!F1027)<br/>total_retrofits_target
      - Metric: total_retrofits_target - Source: A REVIEW OF RESIDENTIAL HEAT DECARBONISATION
      IN IRELAND - 2030: 500000 - Total number of retrofits/renovations up to Target
      Year, National (Calculation!F1028)"
